    "The transport-based UrQMD model is unable to calculate because of the absence of power-law scaling of ΔF q (M) ∝ ΔF 2 (M) q. Consequently, models that exhibit such power-law scaling are required to produce a non-critical baseline for comparison with experimental data.Recently, a study was conducted on the information entropy [164] of the net-proton multiplicity distribution using the hybrid model of ideal fluid dynamics plus UrQMD [165].",
    "The comparisons show that the STAR experimental data extracted from [38] display an enhancement in collision at 20 GeV with respect to the baseline entropy without hydrodynamics, which is consistent with the minimum 2 value reported in [158]."
